    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to extend my sincerest gratitude for your interest in the Senior Developer position at our Austin-based company. We were genuinely impressed by your skills in system design and your excellent cultural fit during the interview process. Your passion and dedication to your craft are truly commendable.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. This decision was not easy, as we believe in the potential of our team and the value you could bring to our company. We understand that this may come as a disappointment, and we want to assure you that this decision was made with the company's best interests in mind.\n\nWe would like to keep the door open for future opportunities and encourage you to apply again when you feel ready. We truly appreciate your interest in our company and the time you invested in the interview process. We wish you all the best in your future endeavors and hope that you continue to find success in your career.\n\nThank you once again for your understanding and for considering us as a potential employer. We hope to have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.",
