      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. that's pretty good. can you make it sound a little less formal? maybe a bit more \"human\" and less like a template, just so it doesn't feel so cold? i want them to feel like we actually liked them.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Just Checking In, [Candidate's Name]\n\nHey [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope you're doing well! I wanted to take a moment to reach out and say a big thank you for considering the Senior Developer role here in Austin. We really appreciated your skills in system design and how well you fit into our team during the interview process. You're a talented individual, and we couldn't help but feel a bit sad to see you go.\n\nAfter some thought, we decided to go with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. We know this might be disappointing, and we want you to know that it wasn't an easy decision. We believe in our team and the direction we're heading, and we felt it was the best choice for us at this time.\n\nBut hey, we're not saying goodbye just yet! We hope you keep an eye out for future opportunities that might be a better fit for you. We really liked working with you, and we hope to have the chance to collaborate again in the future.\n\nThanks again for your time and for considering us. Wishing you all the best in your future endeavors. Let's stay in touch!\n\nTake care,\n[Your Name]",
